      <h2 id="code">The prototype</h2>
      <p>
        The Moverly + OPDA prototype source code is in the cloned
        <a class="resource-link" href="/resource.html?path=source/06-research/smart-data-challenge/code/"><code>source/06-research/smart-data-challenge/code/</code></a>
        directory — a Firebase-backed Node.js application with a React front end.
        The repo has its own <code>CLAUDE.md</code> in case you want a developer-friendly walkthrough.
      </p>

      <h2 id="significance">Why it mattered</h2>
      <p>
        Three things. First, it was the first government-recognised endorsement of
        PDTF as a viable Smart Data sector standard, validating the schema design
        for that programme. Second, it forced a working end-to-end demo across both
        property-pack and identity use cases — exercising parts of the spec that had
        only been theoretical. Third, the post-prize follow-up documents
        (<em>Smart-Data-Challenge-Prize-*</em>) include the cost &amp; timings
        evidence that's been re-used in subsequent MHCLG and DSIT submissions.
      </p>

